metadata.name: ombromanie #118
metadata.description:
‚ÄúHow hands can create the vision that germinates in my mind? And what if the vision directly sprouts from the hands instead of the mind‚Äù, the artist asks.
‚ÄúIs the vision thrown through the shadow of the hands, or is the shadow hands the vision itself?‚Äù, the magician responds.
As an attempt to add a line to this whimsical dialogue, I dropped shadows to cast visions. To my great surprise, the artist and the magician blent into each other‚Ä¶

- - -

‚ÄúOmbromanie‚Äù refers to the art of creating images made by hand shadows. The word and the art (also called ‚Äúshadowgraphy‚Äù) was popularized by french magician F√©licien Trewey in the XIXth century. Sure the shadow art is not so popular nowadays, but it still shares with generative art part of the same mystery and magic. The code projects shapes and colors on a screen to create images; the hands project a shadow on a curtain to create figures.

‚ÄúOmbromanie‚Äù was conceived as a curtain where articulated hands (or better, shadow of hands) throw a firework of shapes, creating a wide range of random compositions. I heard the magician words and I did implement five features for this magical trick:
- the curtain can be entire or hemmed,
- the image oriented the right way up or upside-down,
- one or two hands can be used for the invocation,
- the phatasmagoria reveals itself as syzygy or chaos,
- and climax is reached through twelve ways.
Hands are always present, but in extremely rare cases they could vanish behind the curtain‚Ä¶   

- - - 

This project uses twelve custom color palettes ‚Äì the climaxes.
Ten are inspired after works or body of works by well known generative artists. A kind of tribute for the constant inspiration and creativity of the magicians-artists.
- ‚ÄúHollow‚Äù by @jMarkusiewicz
- ‚ÄúGarden, Monoliths‚Äù by @zancan
- ‚ÄúUninhabitable‚Äù by @pointline_
- ‚ÄúMimizu‚Äù by @qubibien
- ‚Äúaether:Astral Loom‚Äù by @lisaorthstudio
- ‚Äúgestalt‚Äù by @Yazid
- ‚ÄúPerpendicular Inhabitation‚Äù (night) by @StudioYorktown
- ‚ÄúAnaverse‚Äù by @anaglyph_ic
- ‚ÄúTake wing‚Äù by @mwiederrecht
- ‚Äúcontrapuntos‚Äù by @msoriaro
The eleventh palette is named ‚Äúfakewhale‚Äù(@fakewhale_xyz), who, months ago, encouraged me to learn and try code to create generative works. Special thanks to them for the support and dialogue.
The twelfth palette refers to my first long form generative project called ‚Äùth√©ba√Øde‚Äù.

- - -

A small word about the ‚Äúphatasmagoria‚Äù part, which tells about the invisible thread that sews my artistic approach. This part is a modified and extended code I used to create a set of six pieces titled ‚ÄúSketches for unreliable structure‚Äù (Objkt, December 2022). And those were already an echo from a selection of digital (but not coded) works from ‚ÄúThe Queue Structure‚Äù project (Objkt, since May 2022). Finally, The Queue Structure itself was a visual laboratory nourished by my previous practice of abstraction in the tangible world (drawing, collage, monotype, engraving). 

- - -

Press ‚Äús‚Äù in live mode to save the work as a PNG (default 2000 √ó 2000 px).
Add to the URL ‚Äù&size=n‚Äù (number from 3 to 10) to render an image at higher resolution (from 3000 px to 10000 px). It may last for high numbers.
We recommend the use of Chrome browser in order to render properly the texture.

Made with p5js | 2023

metadata.name: Beacon #92
metadata.description:
Thousands of glowing beams, each with its own gradient and disappearing to a path of vanishing points. While the inspiration was figurative, drawn from the Northern Lights, the results have been taken to the abstract. Bold shapes in the foreground draw focus and their simple geometries are elevated to a signal. 

This project was created during a Speed Run over ~24 hours.
Uses WEBGL and may load a little slowly on some machines.

metadata.name: cLAZY MONSTER #15
metadata.description:
This project is Generative Layered PNGs files.

There are 11-Layers mixing together to make many unique 1/1 cLAZY MONSTER.

00-Background - 18 items
01-BackgroundComponent - 14 items
02-Body - 3 items
03-Clothes - 16 items
04-Face_Base - 1 item
05-Face_Level_1 - 20 items
06-Face_Level_2 - 21 items
07-Eyes - 14 items
08-Mouth - 7 items
09-Hands - 10 items
10-Nose - 11 items

So the maximum possibilities to be unique is
18x14x3x16x1x20x21x14x7x10x11 = 54,765,849,600 chances!

Good Luck, cLAZY MONSTER team!

metadata.name: Focal Point #44
metadata.description:
The "Focal Point" series showcases a unique combination of four square artworks arranged in the shape of a plus sign on a textured brown paper. The central motif present in each artwork is an anchor, which also serves as the basis for the color palette throughout the series. The artist began by digitally creating a precisionist central artwork which led to further creation of 28 total artworks, divided into four sets, each set representing a direction.

The symmetry of the resulting form is striking, with the four squares perfectly aligning to create a cohesive and balanced composition. The use of textured brown paper as the background adds depth and dimension to the series, creating an interesting contrast with the clean lines and geometric shapes of the artworks.

The series is an exploration of unity and balance, using the plus sign, a symbol of addition, congruence and equilibrium, to visually represent the idea that by bringing different elements together, a new and harmonious whole can be formed. 

The artist's intent is to convey that despite our differences in physical and intellectual attributes, we are all the same at our core. 

20% of the proceeds from this project will be donated to Southern Exposure, an artist-centered non-profit organization committed to supporting visual artists, that has been in the San Francisco Bay Area since 1974.

For more information regarding my past and upcoming projects, please visit meditationsincolor.com.

metadata.name: Organic Oeuvre #11
metadata.description:
First project on FXHash.

Entirely coded in p5js.

Stochastic strokes while ensuring randomness is consistent; uses 500+ color palettes.

The pieces created by this project are dynamic and change based on the size of the viewing window ("organic"), making each viewing experience unique. 

In case you find a bug, please consider it an easter egg! Write to me on twitter if you think it's a bug and I'll send another couple your way from my reserved :)

Press s to save the image in fullscreen.
